Some reviewers have found the sauce here too thin. The amount of liquid specified strikes me as too great even if the cook turns the pasta into the sauce (not the sauce into the pasta) and heats it for a couple of minutes to let the pasta absorb sauce and get well- coated. There is a similar recipe on this site, "Linguine with Chicken and Walnut Sauce." Both recipes call for bell pepper (though the linguine recipe has 1/2 cup peas instead of a second pepper) , and both suggest 8 oz. pasta. The linguine recipe, however, calls for approximately half the amount of liquid and for a larger amount of chicken. The directions also call for the the ingredients to be mixed into the sauce and heated through.

