Rating: 3
This would be a four-fork recipe if the sauce was thicker. To achieve this end, increase the volume of butter to 3 tablespoons, and when you add the broth and cream cook it down until the cup volume from the broth is gone (just put it on higher heat). Add (one at a time) two egg yolks, stirring furiously with a fork after each addition. Also add 1/2-3/4 cup of cheese instead of the measly quarter cup. Salt and pepper as usual, everything else as usual. This will prevent you from swimming in a pool of thin sauce!

