This was a sensual delight. A perfect late-autmun pasta meal, complemented by a glass of pinot grigio. Per other reviewers' suggestions we doubled the garlic and used white wine to deglaze the pan before adding the garlic and hot pepper. We did use cream (instead of our usual half and half), and added a little yellow bell pepper for extra color, as well as some thinly-sliced mushrooms. The sauce did take a bit longer to thicken. When it was at a point where we were thinking "It's still a litttle too thin," we added the cheese, tossed in the pasta, cooked for another minute... perfect! Please eat this! You will make the world a happier place.

