This was good but can be made even better using a similar recipe I've stumbled on. Use chicken breasts and marinate over night in olive oil, basil, lemon, juice, crushed red pepper, and garlic. For sauce, after sauteeing vegetables, add 1/2 cup each dry white wine and chicken broth and reduce to 2 tbsp. (This process really makes the flavor intense and wonderful!) Then add cream and reduce by half; add parmesan and basil. Grill chicken and cut in strips. Arrange chicken over fettucine and pour sauce over. Enjoy!

